# Deploy & source architecture — LOCKED

Do not deviate from this architecture.

## Commands (canonical)

- **PULL worker source:**  
  `./scripts/with-cloudflare-env.sh npx wrangler r2 object get agent-sam/source/worker-source.js --remote --file /tmp/worker-source.js -c wrangler.production.toml`

- **PUSH worker source:**  
  `./scripts/with-cloudflare-env.sh npx wrangler r2 object put agent-sam/source/worker-source.js --file /tmp/worker-source.js --content-type=application/javascript --remote -c wrangler.production.toml`

- **DEPLOY:** After copying `/tmp/worker-source.js` → `worker.js` in repo root, run `npm run deploy` (never `wrangler deploy` directly).

- **UPLOAD single dashboard HTML:**  
  `./scripts/with-cloudflare-env.sh npx wrangler r2 object put agent-sam/static/dashboard/<file>.html --file=dashboard/<file>.html --content-type=text/html --remote -c wrangler.production.toml`

## Rules

1. **NEVER** run `wrangler deploy` directly — always `npm run deploy`.
2. **NEVER** run wrangler R2/deploy commands without `./scripts/with-cloudflare-env.sh` — it loads the API token.
3. **NEVER** put worker or dashboard source in bucket **iam-platform** — that bucket is for memory/logs only (e.g. `memory/schema-and-records.md`, `memory/daily/*.md`). Worker source and dashboard live in **agent-sam** only.
4. **ALWAYS** upload any changed dashboard file to R2 (agent-sam) **before** running `npm run deploy`.
5. Repo root **worker.js** is what gets deployed. The R2 object **agent-sam/source/worker-source.js** is a backup only; deploy uses the repo file.

Reference: `docs/LOCATIONS_AND_DEPLOY_AUDIT.md`.
